def _get_grouper(
    obj,
    key=None,
    axis=0,
    level=None,
    sort=True,
    observed=False,
    mutated=False,
    validate=True,
):
    group_axis = obj._get_axis(axis)
    
    # Check if the grouping is by columns
    if key is not None and axis == 1:
        if is_list_like(key):
            # Group by multiple columns
            keys = key
        else:
            keys = [key]
        groupings = [
            Grouping(
                group_axis,
                obj[key],
                obj=obj,
                name=key,
                level=level,
                sort=sort,
                observed=observed,
                in_axis=True,
            )
            for key in keys
        ]
        
        # Create the internals grouper
        grouper = BaseGrouper(group_axis, groupings, sort=sort, mutated=mutated)
        
        return grouper, [], obj
